WEBVTT

00:01.760 --> 00:03.394
(woman) Put the gun down, Bethany.

00:03.396 --> 00:06.596
How are you... You're dead.

00:06.599 --> 00:10.067
I told you I wanted to start over,

00:10.069 --> 00:12.403
to disappear...
and I needed the world...

00:12.405 --> 00:14.905
- You faked your suicide?
- Yes.

00:14.907 --> 00:17.541
And I'm sorry, I can't imagine
what I put you through.

00:17.543 --> 00:20.277
No, you can't.

00:20.279 --> 00:23.681
I was so afraid of someone
finding out what we did,

00:23.683 --> 00:25.483
of losing my freedom.

00:25.485 --> 00:26.984
- I can't...
- Where have you been?

00:26.986 --> 00:31.822
Paraguay, some remote
village outside San Lorenzo.

00:31.824 --> 00:33.157
Why did you come back? Why...

00:33.159 --> 00:34.659
They found me.

00:34.661 --> 00:37.062
Someone knows about Daylight.

00:37.064 --> 00:40.131
They made a play.
I barely escaped with my life.

00:40.133 --> 00:42.858
I need help. I need you and Carter.

00:42.898 --> 00:44.331
Carter is dead.

00:44.333 --> 00:46.566
Oh, God.

00:46.568 --> 00:49.002
They're coming after all of us.

00:49.004 --> 00:50.537
I need new passports.

00:50.539 --> 00:53.907
I need to secure a safe passage
into another country.

00:53.909 --> 00:55.715
- I need...
- Money.

00:56.878 --> 00:59.372
You came back to me
because you need money.

01:00.048 --> 01:02.248
I know you're angry and I know
I've put you through hell,

01:02.250 --> 01:04.044
but look at where we are.

01:04.753 --> 01:08.221
I love you, Bethany, but I had to run.

01:08.223 --> 01:10.890
If you were smart you would do the same.

01:10.892 --> 01:12.258
I don't run.

01:14.562 --> 01:16.563
Well, at least help me then, please.

01:23.638 --> 01:24.671
Hey, Patterson.

01:24.673 --> 01:26.172
You want to play a game?

01:26.174 --> 01:27.240
Love games.

01:27.242 --> 01:28.475
Don't get too excited.

01:28.477 --> 01:29.743
It's not one of your
wizard and elf games

01:29.745 --> 01:31.244
that take four hours to finish.

01:31.246 --> 01:33.580
Well, D&D doesn't ever really finish.

01:33.582 --> 01:34.581
What do these numbers mean to you?

01:34.583 --> 01:37.283
34, 30, 21, 9...

01:37.285 --> 01:38.652
Oh.

01:38.654 --> 01:40.920
- 41, 28...
- Oh! Oh.

01:40.922 --> 01:42.956
- ...13, 7.
- Yes-yes-yes-yes.

01:42.958 --> 01:44.991
I have been obsessed with
these and I haven't been able

01:44.993 --> 01:46.119
to figure this out.

01:46.121 --> 01:48.962
Yeah, I was reading about Levi Hart...

01:48.964 --> 01:51.731
The running back from Hudson
University who got kicked off

01:51.733 --> 01:53.400
the team for drugs...

01:53.402 --> 01:54.460
yesterday.

01:54.736 --> 01:57.604
Anyway, the article lists
the ups and downs

01:57.606 --> 01:59.139
of the football program.

01:59.141 --> 02:02.175
The ups being the last four
national championship wins

02:02.177 --> 02:03.510
and their scores.

02:05.680 --> 02:07.180
34 to 30.

02:07.182 --> 02:08.681
21 to 9.

02:08.684 --> 02:09.983
41 to 28.

02:09.985 --> 02:12.185
13 to 7.

02:12.187 --> 02:13.420
You're like some kind of wizard.

02:13.422 --> 02:14.688
What do we do now, elf?

02:14.690 --> 02:17.090
Actually, I am a gnome cleric.

02:17.092 --> 02:20.427
Now, we just have
to figure out why this tattoo

02:20.429 --> 02:22.462
is pointing to the Hudson
football program.

02:24.632 --> 02:25.733
I thought you hated tea.

02:26.435 --> 02:27.634
Well, it's grown on me.

02:27.636 --> 02:29.169
Glad you came over to my side.

02:29.171 --> 02:31.337
What's with the bowtie, Bill Nye?

02:31.339 --> 02:32.972
Has anybody heard from Weller?

02:32.974 --> 02:33.973
Yeah.

02:33.975 --> 02:35.642
(Weller) Sorry, I'm late.

02:35.644 --> 02:36.976
(Bethany) Go ahead, Patterson.

02:36.978 --> 02:38.945
Okay. Well, first and foremost,

02:38.947 --> 02:40.880
Tasha unlocked a tattoo.

02:42.283 --> 02:43.850
Wow, what have we got?

02:43.852 --> 02:45.885
(Zapata) The last four
championship scores

02:45.887 --> 02:47.821
from Hudson University's football team,

02:47.823 --> 02:50.724
they're on Jane's lower abdomen,
hidden in the fingertips

02:50.726 --> 02:52.058
of the handprint tattoo.

02:52.060 --> 02:53.626
That's different.

02:53.628 --> 02:54.861
What could that be about?

02:54.863 --> 02:56.396
Hudson was under league investigation

02:56.398 --> 02:57.964
last year for scholarship fraud.

02:57.966 --> 02:59.332
A lot of top ranked schools

02:59.334 --> 03:00.734
get investigated... it's pretty common.

03:00.736 --> 03:02.302
A few weeks in, the lead investigator,

03:02.304 --> 03:03.870
Ed Mackey, said he didn't

03:03.872 --> 03:06.339
find any problems with
the scholarship system.

03:06.341 --> 03:10.677
So, six months later, this guy
becomes the VP of a big-time

03:10.679 --> 03:13.747
athletic apparel company,
and now he's being reviewed.

03:13.749 --> 03:15.648
Because the former CEO of said company

03:15.650 --> 03:18.218
is now the current
president of Hudson University,

03:18.220 --> 03:20.186
Karen Morris.

03:20.188 --> 03:22.756
So, the investigator might have
been paid off with a cushy job.

03:22.758 --> 03:24.524
It's no big deal.

03:24.526 --> 03:26.226
Why draw our attention to that?

03:26.228 --> 03:29.095
This clearly points
to Hudson's athletic program.

03:29.097 --> 03:30.830
I know the defensive coordinator
over there,

03:30.832 --> 03:32.098
I went to his camps as a kid.

03:32.100 --> 03:33.500
Would he be willing to talk to us?

03:33.502 --> 03:35.401
I don't see why not. He's a good guy.

03:35.403 --> 03:36.936
He used to give me
rides home from practice

03:36.938 --> 03:38.371
when my mom was running late.

03:38.373 --> 03:39.552
We stayed in touch.

03:39.554 --> 03:41.074
Good, head out.

03:41.076 --> 03:42.505
Let me know what you find.

03:46.547 --> 03:48.414
(distant chatter)

03:50.217 --> 03:51.384
The only thing I'm good for here

03:51.386 --> 03:53.386
is running a lean three-four defense.

03:53.388 --> 03:55.455
I don't have anything to do
with the scholarships.

03:55.457 --> 03:57.257
I know, coach, I just...

03:57.259 --> 03:59.793
We got a tip that there was
something off in the program.

03:59.772 --> 04:01.588
Any idea what that could be about?

04:01.830 --> 04:03.019
Something off?

04:03.598 --> 04:04.764
Were they more specific?

04:04.766 --> 04:06.299
It's hard to explain.

04:06.301 --> 04:08.434
They run a tight ship here, Edgar.

04:08.436 --> 04:10.937
Been investigated a few times,
nothing sticks.

04:10.939 --> 04:13.239
Coach is a good guy, disciplined.

04:13.241 --> 04:15.475
I can't imagine what that
something off might be.

04:15.477 --> 04:16.910
What about this Levi Hart kid?

04:16.911 --> 04:18.310
His story's been all over the news.

04:18.313 --> 04:20.046
Gifted athlete, troubled kid.

04:20.048 --> 04:21.648
Nothing more to it than that.

04:21.649 --> 04:24.017
Karen Morris. I'm the president
of the university.

04:24.019 --> 04:25.518
Would you mind telling me
what this is all about?

04:25.520 --> 04:27.086
Karen, this is Edgar Reade.

04:27.088 --> 04:28.688
He's one of my favorite camp kids.

04:28.690 --> 04:31.024
Still helps out in the summer
when he's not too busy.

04:31.026 --> 04:32.058
Nice to meet you.

04:32.060 --> 04:33.092
It's always a pleasure to meet

04:33.094 --> 04:34.661
one of Coach Jones's protégés,

04:34.663 --> 04:36.930
but this doesn't feel
like a social visit.

04:36.932 --> 04:39.499
Uh, Special Agent Kurt Weller
with the FBI.

04:39.501 --> 04:40.954
And this is my team.

04:40.981 --> 04:42.460
And are you talking to Coach Jones

04:42.437 --> 04:43.870
in any sort of official capacity?

04:43.872 --> 04:45.839
- Yes, but we...
- Then I'm afraid I'm going to

04:45.841 --> 04:47.440
end this conversation immediately.

04:47.442 --> 04:49.142
Please direct any requests
to talk to our personnel

04:49.144 --> 04:50.944
to my office. Let's go.

04:50.946 --> 04:53.515
- Good to see you.
- Good seeing you, coach.

04:53.949 --> 04:56.049
(distant shouting)

04:56.759 --> 04:58.231
They're hiding something, Reade.

04:58.587 --> 05:00.353
Could be, just doesn't
seem tattoo worthy.

05:00.355 --> 05:02.088
Scholarship fraud
isn't that bug of a deal.

05:02.090 --> 05:03.089
Which probably means it's probably more

05:03.091 --> 05:04.669
than scholarship fraud.

05:05.360 --> 05:07.093
(Patterson) Hey, are you guys there?

05:07.095 --> 05:08.962
Patterson. Go.

05:08.964 --> 05:10.137
<i>Any luck?</i>

05:10.799 --> 05:13.800
No, they lawyered up.
Did you find anything?

05:13.802 --> 05:15.869
I looked into terminated <i>scholarships</i>

05:15.871 --> 05:18.104
(radio static) and for any other
information <i>I could get.</i>

05:18.106 --> 05:20.344
And? Patterson?

05:20.842 --> 05:22.375
I lost the comms.

05:22.377 --> 05:23.543
Anyone else got her?

05:23.545 --> 05:24.978
Mm-mm.

05:24.980 --> 05:26.446
We must be in a dead zone.

05:26.448 --> 05:29.182
(distant gunfire)

05:29.184 --> 05:30.383
Run, run!

05:30.385 --> 05:31.684
He's got a gun!

05:31.686 --> 05:33.686
- (crowd screaming)
- Run!

05:33.688 --> 05:35.555
- Inside?
- Yeah.

05:35.557 --> 05:37.290
(Weller) Active shooter! Active shooter!

05:39.293 --> 05:42.295
♪

05:42.350 --> 05:49.399
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

05:54.953 --> 05:55.979
(man) Lauren?

05:56.160 --> 05:57.706
_

05:57.823 --> 05:59.245
Lauren.

06:00.791 --> 06:03.282
Just wanted to make sure you
had the opportunity to share

06:03.284 --> 06:04.626
before we wrap things up.

06:05.650 --> 06:06.963
I'm good.

06:06.965 --> 06:09.366
Well, it's customary for people
to share in their first meet.

06:09.368 --> 06:13.387
Customary, but not mandatory, right?

06:13.805 --> 06:15.636
That's right.

06:16.241 --> 06:17.637
I'm good.

06:18.710 --> 06:21.745
Part of being here is admitting
that you're not good.

06:24.815 --> 06:26.235
Let's wrap it up then.

06:27.261 --> 06:29.585
(all) God give us the serenity

06:29.588 --> 06:32.522
to accept the things we cannot change.

06:32.524 --> 06:33.990
- The courage...
- Take care, man.

06:36.027 --> 06:38.695
- It's nice meeting you.
- Good luck with everything.

06:39.764 --> 06:40.997
I mean, I'll come back.

06:40.999 --> 06:42.399
Oh, okay.

06:48.509 --> 06:50.774
Isn't that like bringing a bottle to AA?

06:51.801 --> 06:54.277
I have enough self-control
to read the sports pages.

06:54.279 --> 06:57.547
I just flip past the point
spreads to get to the stories.

07:00.656 --> 07:01.967
You finished with that?

07:02.487 --> 07:04.454
(students screaming)

07:04.456 --> 07:06.189
(gunfire)

07:06.191 --> 07:07.390
Patterson!

07:07.392 --> 07:09.987
Patterson! We have no comms.

07:09.989 --> 07:11.628
Shooter must be jamming our signal.

07:12.897 --> 07:14.464
Landline's dead.

07:14.466 --> 07:16.566
All right, I'll take
the upper levels with Jane.

07:16.568 --> 07:18.602
You two, clear this floor. All right?

07:18.627 --> 07:19.836
On it.

07:19.838 --> 07:21.504
Exit through the lobby.

07:21.506 --> 07:23.006
- Go.
- Exit through the lobby.

07:23.008 --> 07:24.710
Get to safety guys, get outside.

07:24.712 --> 07:25.809
Move.

07:25.811 --> 07:27.310
Go, keep going.

07:29.680 --> 07:31.191
I'll go this way.

07:31.891 --> 07:32.981
All right.

